**[Understanding Deep Learning Requires Rethinking Generalization](https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.03530)** - Explores the generalization capabilities of deep learning models, which relates to the emergence of structures in algorithmic learning.
**[The Loss Surfaces of Multilayer Networks](https://arxiv.org/abs/1412.0233)** - Investigates the landscape of loss functions in deep learning, which is crucial in understanding how emergent structures form in algorithmic learning systems.
**[Neural Turing Machines](https://arxiv.org/abs/1410.5401)** - Introduces a neural network architecture that can learn algorithms and exhibit emergent structures in its learning process.
10:
**[Stability and Change in Concept Learning](https://www.jstor.org/stable/1128191)** - Explores the balance between stability and change in concept learning processes.
**[Adaptive Concept Learning](https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF00992325)** - Investigates how adaptive learning systems acquire and retain concepts over time.
**[Learning and Adaptation in Autonomous Agents](https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.5555/2254993.2254995)** - Discusses learning and adaptation mechanisms in autonomous agents to maintain stability in conceptual knowledge.
